            p These special character literals can be placed anywhere within a string and will be treated as a single character. For instance:

            pre(class="bg-light")
                code. 
                  let text = "This is the letter sigma: \u03a3."

            p In this example, the variable <code>text</code> contains 28 characters, even though the escape sequence is 6 characters long. The escape sequence represents one character and is counted as such.

            p You can find the length of any string using the <code>length</code> property like this:

            pre(class="bg-light")
                code. 
                    console.log(text.length); // 28

            p The <code>length</code> property gives the number of 16-bit characters in the string.
        
